<h1>Free Form Magic</h1>
<p>Free Form Magic is the foundation of the magic system in my Traveller games. To do a magic check, you use your Psi stat against the type of magics spell DC, as well as some modifiers as decided by your Referee and the type of Magic you are trying to cast.</p>
<p>Free Form Magic operates starts at DC 5, and for each word you add into the spell you increase the DM by 1. Each spell you cast requries at least 3 words (the Plane you're casting from, the Action you're casting, and What you're casting on.), so really the minimum Free Form Magic DC is 8+. You can increase this by adding modifier words to your spell, but it will increase the spell DC. As well, you use the number of Psi Points equal to the number of words in your spell.</p>
<p>So while Free Form Magic may be the most open to abuse, it is both hard to cast, and very draining to use.</p>
<h2>Composing a Free Form Spell</h2>
<p>To compose a Free Form Spell, you require at least three words: The Plane, The Action, The Target. You can optionally choose to add any modifiers you would like.</p>
<p>The Plane is which plane of existance you are casting from, this is also the skill you add to your Psi cast. </p>
<p>The Action is roughly what you are hoping to accomplish with this spell, it is fairly vague so as to allow the player and the Referee to work together to decided on how it should work.</p>
<p>The Target is what or who you are targeting, what sort of broad type of thing is it.</p>
<p>The Modifiers allow you to adjust your spell, fine tuning it to be as percise as you need from the very broad and generic to something more surgical for your needs at that time.</p>
<p>If you fail to cast your spell, roll on the <a href="/Rules/Magic/Perils"> Perils Table</a> applying the effect of your roll to the result on the table.</p>
<p>The skills usesd to a cast a spell are named after the 5 planes of existance. Thus they are : Void, Aether, Material, Nether, Abyss/</p>
<p>The final casting stat line looks like: 2D6 + CASTSING_PLANE + PSI + Modifiers > 5 + NUMBER_OF_WORDS</p>

